<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="727" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[1987,2581,2765,3187]" lastBlockId="19.[1378,2579,3195,3267]" pageId="19" pageNumber="727">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1987,2264,2958,2991]" pageId="19" pageNumber="727">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body mean 203 mm (males) and 200 mm (females), tail mean 191 mm (males) and 192 mm (females); weight mean c.285 g. Dorsum and tail of the Mindanao Squirrel are dark gray. Hairs have a black base, buffy middle, and a black tip. Mid-dorsal area is darker, nose and eye region are rufous, thighs and dorsal parts of feet are rufous gray. Venter, including lower surface oflegs,is ashy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
